Rating: 1
I generally make recipes as they're written the first time I make them. What I discovered with this recipe is that there's way too much brandy for the amount of cream. Even after the sauce boiled, the brandy flavor was still too strong. There should be only a splash of brandy (or cognag) to add a little spark of flavor.

Rating: 3
This is easy, and it tastes really good. Not amazing, but quite good given the ease. The timing on getting the breast cooked and the sauce reduced can be tough--there are just so many variables here, like mushroom moisture, how hot your stove is, how thick the chicken breast is, etc. So you may need to add water or stock, or you might need to take the breasts out when they're done and further reduce the sauce. On top of that, I think it's pretty hard to know when chicken is done just by touch, yet it's easily overdone, which makes this recipe not as easy as one might think. If you're like me in that way, you have to cut into it a few times or use a meat thermometer, both of which are a minor pain.

