Rating: 3
Made this for a dinner party. Highly recommend making it a day in advance as the flavours melded together better by the second day. I pounded the chicken slightly just to even out the thickness for even cooking and dredged in flour. I prepared it on the stove and the next day I just popped it in the oven and cooked it at a relatively low heat. The chicken was incredibly moist. I used shallots instead of onions and I opted out of the dehydrated mushrooms due to the texture issue. I chose button mushrooms which I found to be quite mild tasting. Perhaps mixing them with a richer meatier mushroom might help. I also added some chicken stock to taste. Salt and pepper is necessary. I served this with Duchess Potatoes where were devine! Comfort Food for sure...but for the milder palates.

