Rating: 4
This is a great recipe.I have been making my own version of it for years.Here are some maybe helpful hints for those who had problems with the sauce.First,when you add cream(should be 35%) you should first denature it by bringing to a "first boil" this will prevent it from curdling will also make your dish last longer cause it will not go sour.I always add a pinch of nutmeg to any cream sauces I make.I too use olive oil and very little butter.Butter gets toxic at high temperatures,so you should always add it at the end to blend in rather than cook with it.when sauteing the mushrooms,I use just a bit of olive oil and a bit of butter.My preferred dried mushrooms are the dried porchini,or the cepes.These give a fantastic aroma and flavour to the dish. Your problem of having difficulty in thickening the sauce is because you put too much liquid.If you have so done, and the chicken is already cooked, remove them from the pan,then boil down the liquid/now you can add the cream/mushroom sauce,and return the chicken to the pan to simmer for a few minutes.I hope this has helped those who were disappointed.dont hesitate to ask further questions.It will be my pleasure to respond.Gina1139@yahoo.com

