Rating: 4
This is a lovely dish. For those reviewers who were commenting that the sauce is too thin; I wonder if they weren't patient enough in allowing the mushroom liquid to evaporate. I waited until it was paste-like, added the cream, brandy, and reserved soaking liquid, brought it to a gentle boil, and it took about the 8 minutes that the recipe mentioned for it to thicken right up. I would recommend that you slightly flatten the chicken breasts so they are about the same thickeness throughout. Look an earlier reviewer, I added garlic. (Two cloves, chopped.) Served with wide egg noodles and green peas. Used two types of dried mushrooms (porcini and oyster). Very good, and I will definitely put this on my "favorites" list.

Rating: 3
An oldie but a goodie - rich and very flavourful. I used 6 chicken thighs so increased the amount of broth, cream and brandy by one half and added 3 cloves minced garlic to the onion and 'shroom mix. Simmered the sauce for 15 min. to thicken/reduce and added 2-3 dashes ground nutmeg (so good with mushroom dishes). The dried 'shrooms add so much earthy/hearty flavour, so do not omit them. Poured the finished sauce over the browned chicken and baked at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. The thighs were moist/tender with ample sauce of good thickness/consistency. Calorie laden and not a healthy dish, but delicious and very satisfying. We can't always eat "twigs, leaves and pebbles" and all deserve a guilty pleasure every now and again! Cheers!

